Here are the authoritative public test cases for feature4_extract_payload:
{
  "description": "Render the JSON arguments array carried by a decoded message back to a compact JSON string. For an event message the leading event-name element has already been consumed, so only the remaining arguments are rendered; for an acknowledgement message the full stored array is rendered as-is.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "extract_payload",
        "type": "Event",
        "text": "[\"event\",1]"
      },
      "expected_output": "payload=[1]\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "extract_payload",
        "type": "Ack",
        "text": "[\"event\",\"hello\",{\"user\":\"admin\",\"password\":\"test\"}]"
      },
      "expected_output": "payload=[\"event\",\"hello\",{\"user\":\"admin\",\"password\":\"test\"}]\n"
    }
  ]
}

Here are the authoritative public test cases for feature3_2_decode_binary:
{
  "description": "Decode an inbound binary message that spans a leading text frame plus one or more raw attachment frames. The text frame declares the attachment count, optional namespace, optional acknowledgement id and the JSON payload (with binary placeholders). The message is only produced once all declared attachment frames have arrived; until then nothing is emitted.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "451-[\"1 params\",{\"_placeholder\":true,\"num\":0}]"
          },
          {
            "bytes": [
              0
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=binary_event\nevent=1 params\nattachment_count=1\ndata=[{\"_placeholder\":true,\"num\":0}]\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "451-/test,[\"1 params\",{\"_placeholder\":true,\"num\":0}]"
          },
          {
            "bytes": [
              0
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=binary_event\nevent=1 params\nnamespace=/test\nattachment_count=1\ndata=[{\"_placeholder\":true,\"num\":0}]\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "451-30[\"1 params\",{\"_placeholder\":true,\"num\":0}]"
          },
          {
            "bytes": [
              0
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=binary_event\nevent=1 params\nid=30\nattachment_count=1\ndata=[{\"_placeholder\":true,\"num\":0}]\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "461-6[{\"_placeholder\":true,\"num\":0}]"
          },
          {
            "bytes": [
              0
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=binary_ack\nid=6\nattachment_count=1\ndata=[{\"_placeholder\":true,\"num\":0}]\n"
    }
  ]
}

Here are the authoritative public test cases for feature3_1_decode_text:
{
  "description": "Decode a single inbound text frame into a structured message. The numeric prefix selects the kind (heartbeat ping/pong, transport opened handshake, namespace connected/disconnected, event, acknowledgement, connect error). Optional namespace, acknowledgement id, event name and JSON argument payload are extracted from their wire positions; unrecognized or empty frames yield no message.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "2"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=ping\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "0{\"sid\":\"wOuAvDB9Jj6yE0VrAL8N\",\"upgrades\":[\"websocket\"],\"pingInterval\":25000,\"pingTimeout\":30000}"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=opened\nsid=wOuAvDB9Jj6yE0VrAL8N\nping_interval=25000\nping_timeout=30000\nupgrades=websocket\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "40{\"sid\":\"aMA_EmVTuzpgR16PAc4w\"}"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=connected\nsid=aMA_EmVTuzpgR16PAc4w\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "40/test,{\"sid\":\"aMA_EmVTuzpgR16PAc4w\"}"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=connected\nnamespace=/test\nsid=aMA_EmVTuzpgR16PAc4w\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "42/test,[\"hi\",\"V3: onAny\"]"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=event\nevent=hi\nnamespace=/test\ndata=[\"V3: onAny\"]\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "42/test,17[\"cool\"]"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=event\nevent=cool\nnamespace=/test\nid=17\ndata=[]\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "431[\"nice\"]"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=ack\nid=1\ndata=[\"nice\"]\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "decode",
        "eio": 4,
        "frames": [
          {
            "text": "44{\"message\":\"Authentication error2\"}"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "type=error\nerror_message=Authentication error2\n"
    }
  ]
}

Here are the authoritative public test cases for feature2_4_encode_connect:
{
  "description": "Encode the namespace-connection frame. Under protocol v3 the default namespace produces no frame (none is sent), while a named namespace yields a connect frame that carries the namespace and, optionally, the connection query string. Under protocol v4 the default namespace always produces a connect frame, an auth object is serialized inline as JSON, and connection queries are not embedded in this frame.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "encode_connect",
        "eio": 3,
        "namespace": null,
        "auth": null,
        "query": null
      },
      "expected_output": "frame=null\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "encode_connect",
        "eio": 3,
        "namespace": "/test",
        "auth": null,
        "query": null
      },
      "expected_output": "frame=40/test,\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "encode_connect",
        "eio": 3,
        "namespace": "/test",
        "auth": null,
        "query": {
          "key": "value"
        }
      },
      "expected_output": "frame=40/test?key=value,\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "encode_connect",
        "eio": 4,
        "namespace": null,
        "auth": null,
        "query": null
      },
      "expected_output": "frame=40\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "encode_connect",
        "eio": 4,
        "namespace": null,
        "auth": {
          "userId": 1
        },
        "query": null
      },
      "expected_output": "frame=40{\"userId\":1}\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "encode_connect",
        "eio": 4,
        "namespace": "/test",
        "auth": {
          "userId": 1
        },
        "query": null
      },
      "expected_output": "frame=40/test,{\"userId\":1}\n"
    }
  ]
}

Here are the authoritative public test cases for feature2_3_encode_ack:
{
  "description": "Encode an outbound acknowledgement message replying to a previously received id-bearing request. There is no event name; the argument array is emitted directly, preceded by the acknowledgement id (and namespace when present). Binary arguments become placeholders plus ordered attachments and switch the frame to the binary-ack prefix.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "encode_ack",
        "eio": 4,
        "packet_id": 0,
        "namespace": null,
        "data": [
          "string",
          1,
          true,
          null
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "frame=430[\"string\",1,true,null]\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "encode_ack",
        "eio": 4,
        "packet_id": 23,
        "namespace": "/test",
        "data": [
          "string",
          1,
          true,
          null
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "frame=43/test,23[\"string\",1,true,null]\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "encode_ack",
        "eio": 4,
        "packet_id": 8964,
        "namespace": "/test",
        "data": [
          123456.789,
          {
            "User": "test",
            "Password": "hello"
          },
          {
            "Size": 2023,
            "Name": "test.txt",
            "Bytes": {
              "$bytes": [
                240,
                159,
                144,
                174,
                240,
                159,
                141,
                186
              ]
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "frame=461-/test,8964[123456.789,{\"User\":\"test\",\"Password\":\"hello\"},{\"Size\":2023,\"Name\":\"test.txt\",\"Bytes\":{\"_placeholder\":true,\"num\":0}}]\nattachment=240,159,144,174,240,159,141,186\n"
    }
  ]
}

